Phat Kii Mao
 - Andy Ricker
 
2 garlic cloves
2 red Thai chiles
2 tbsp lard or soybean oil
8 oz beef sirloin, thinly sliced
1 tbsp pickled green peppercorns
1 green Thai chile, crushed
2" piece galangal, peeled and julienned
½ long green chile, thinly sliced into rings
½ long red chile, thinly sliced into rings
2 oz (⅓ c) long beans, cut into 1½" batons
½ c sliced baby corn
½ yellow onion, thinly sliced
1 tbsp oyster sauce
1 tsp fish sauce, plus more to taste
1 tsp soy sauce
1 tsp granulated sugar
6 tbsp beef stock
½ c holy basil leaves
1 tsp Lao Khao or any neutral rice liquor

Using a mortar and pestle, crush the garlic and red Thai chiles into a paste. In a large wok, heat the lard over medium-high heat. Add the chile paste and the beef, and stir-fry until fragrant and golden, 2-3 min. Add the pickled green peppercorns, green Thai chile, galangal, long green chile and long red chile, then stir-fry until fragrant, 1 m. Add the long beans, baby corn and onions, and cook until the vegetables are tender, 3-4 min.Stir in the sauces and sugar, followed by the beef stock. Bring to a boil, then remove from the heat and stir in the basil leaves and Lao Kho. Adjust the seasoning with fish sauce, then divide between plates and serve.

